Put the salmon in a bowl and combine the first maple syrup and soy sauce.  Marinate the salmon for about 20 minutes.  Place the salmon on a sheet pan.  Brush the raw salmon with the first maple syrup.  Bake it in the oven at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.  Brush the salmon again with the second syrup.  Return to the oven and bake 2 more minutes.  Check the temp and make sure it is done.  You can brush more of the second syrup on after it is done.  Just don't use the same stuff you used on the raw salmon!
